WE BREAK DATA BARRIERS AND BUILD A NEW HEALTH ECONOMY TO IMPROVE HEALTHCARE WORLDWIDE.
Grapevine World unites companies that have the common aim of standardizing data transfer. So, together Grapevine World technology suppliers, Grapevine World providers and Grapevine World integrators (system integrators) make global data transfer possible – based on IHE standards.

HOW ARE WE SET UP ?

Grapevine World is an international holding company with the two business segments Marketplace and Backbone. Grapevine World coordinates transregional activities such as marketing.

The national companies (Grapevine World Nationals) are responsible for implementing and managing standardized digitalization projects in the specific countries.

WHAT ARE THE OBJECTIVES ?
// INTEROPERABILITY

The objective of the Grapevine World Initiative is to enable the increasingly important topic of interoperability in all industries by standardized data exchange, which relies on the IHE methodology, thus replacing expensive and inefficient proprietary systems.

// OPENING UP NEW MARKETS

In addition, the Grapevine World marketplace offers companies of every size of enterprise the possibility to enter new markets.

// STRENGTHENING THE IHE COMMUNITY

In addition, the IHE community is being strengthened on a global scale in order to continue to drive forward the leading ongoing global standardization of IT.

HOW DO CITIZENS BENEFIT FROM THE INITIATIVE?

Citizens benefit from the simplification of processes and procedures and consequently receive universal access to their own personal data with complete control and autonomy (example from healthcare: digital patient files, overview and sharing of information at any time by smartphone). Interoperable solutions continue to strongly contribute to cost reductions. Thus, prices fall for end customers as well.

THE ADVANTAGES AT A GLANCE
  • Efficient and sustainable use of public and private funds through standardized data exchange (e.g. cost-saving on administration)
  • Immediate usage of an existing global infrastructure
  • No media gaps through the use of a standardized healthcare system (no USB drive, no CD)
  • Exchange of patient data between private (e.g. Austrian Health) and public (e.g. ELGA) healthcare files
  • Exchange and bundling of various different kinds of data (activity data, vital data, clinical data, care manager data)
  • Ultimate security through decentralized storage of data
  • Different manufacturers – the One Stop Shop principle
